'''妇女主义'''（Womanism）是基于有色人种女性（尤其是{{le|黑人女性|black women}}）的历史和日常生活经验的社会理论。根据妇女主义学者Layli Maparyan的说法，它力求“恢复人与环境/自然之间的平衡，并使人类生活与精神层面保持平衡”<ref name="Reader">{{cite book|last1=Phillips|first1=Layli|title=The Womanist Reader|date=2006|publisher=Routledge|location=New York and Abingdon}}</ref><!--loc="Introduction. Womanism: On Its Own"-->。作家[[爱丽丝·沃克|爱丽丝·沃克]]（Alice Walker）在1979年的短篇小说《拆散》（Coming Apart）中创造了“妇女主义者”（womanist）一词{{sfn|Phillips|2006|p=xix |loc="Introduction. Womanism: On Its Own"}}<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.encyclopedia.com/social-sciences/encyclopedias-almanacs-transcripts-and-maps/womanism |title=Womanism |website=www.encyclopedia.com |access-date=2018-02-26 |archive-date=2018-06-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180616204300/https://www.encyclopedia.com/social-sciences/encyclopedias-almanacs-transcripts-and-maps/womanism |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=":0">{{citation|last=Walker|first=Alice|title=Coming Apart}}.{{full citation needed|date=October 2019}}</ref>。

